commit_message:
Add a helper function to find the config section by name

Add a helper function to find the config section whose name is as
specified for deploy engines or server providers. For example:

the config is:
{
    'name': 'Fake1',
    'provider': {
        'name': 'Fake2',
        'host_provider': {
            'name': 'Fake3',
        }
    }
}

If the name is 'Fake1', it will return the whole config.
If the name is 'Fake2', it will return config['provider']
If the name is 'Fake3', it will return config['provider']['host_provider']

Change-Id: Iddd69a04b6c969c73cb3b54c9f73620f6a4f2399
